    "docHtml": "<p>A wooden flail adapted from the threshing-floor—two sticks joined by a leather strap or short chain. Farmers and militia press the grainflail into service as a combat weapon, swinging it to deliver rapid strikes with unpredictable arc. Light and accessible, it favors skirmishers and levy troops who lack coin for proper arms.</p>\n",
